<div class="tip-card">🤝 <strong>Hordozás:</strong> Shift + Jobb klikk entitáson → elkezded hordozni azt az entitást. Hasznos állatok áthelyezéséhez, NPC partnerek hordozásához és kis élőlények elmozdításához.</div>

<h3 id="debug-keys">Debug Billentyűk</h3>
<div class="tip-card">🔧 <strong>F3+H</strong> — Részletes Tooltip mód: tárgyak tartóssági százaléka látható, bűvölés ID számok megjelennek, belső item adatok láthatók.</div>
<div class="tip-card">🔧 <strong>F3+B</strong> — Hitbox megjelenítés: összes entitás és blokk ütközési doboza látható. Hasznos mob AI teszteléshez és precíz építkezéshez.</div>
</div>

<div data-lang="en">
<h2 id="game-modes-en">Game Modes — Simple vs Hardcore</h2>
<p>MITE:BE has two fundamental game modes. <strong>Simple (Survivor)</strong> mode is for learning and exploration, while <strong>Hardcore</strong> is the ultimate, brutal challenge. There are <em>many</em> mechanical differences between them!</p>

<div class="warning-box">⚠️ <strong>This wiki applies to BOTH modes by default.</strong> Where mode-specific differences exist, they are explicitly marked. If not indicated, the mechanic works the same in both modes.</div>

<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Mechanic</th><th>Simple (Survivor)</th><th>Hardcore</th></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Torch burnout</strong></td><td>No time-based burnout, but rain extinguishes!</td><td>✅ Burn out after 3 days + rain extinguishes</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Leaf passability</strong></td><td>❌ Solid — can stand on them</td><td>✅ Passable — player falls through (extra blocks required for tree climbing)</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Gravel generation</strong></td><td>75% chance</td><td>55% chance</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Shield blocking</strong></td><td>Normal chance, 50% damage reduction</td><td>−3% block chance, only 20% damage reduction</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Ore clusters</strong></td><td>✅ Generate normally</td><td>❌ No ore clusters generate</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Ore above Y40</strong></td><td>Normal distribution</td><td>Only Adamantium ore found above Y40</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Zombie rain spawning</strong></td><td>❌ Don't spawn in rain</td><td>✅ Spawn in rain</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Mob spawn Y0-10 in light</strong></td><td>❌ Don't spawn in light</td><td>✅ Spawn even in light</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Blood Moon mutant zombies</strong></td><td>Normal spawn rate</td><td>Double spawn rate</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Ender Dragon HP</strong></td><td colspan="2">The local <code>mobs.json</code> lists 200 HP; the 100/1000 mode split is not confirmed here</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Enderman and water</strong></td><td>Afraid of water (vanilla)</td><td>NOT afraid of water!</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Death</strong></td><td>Respawn possible</td><td>Permadeath — world is deleted</td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Post-death debuff</strong></td><td colspan="2">Both modes: <strong>Severe Injury</strong> status effect applied on respawn <abbr class="src-cl" title="Source: mod changelog — not personally verified">📜 changelog</abbr></td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Zombie revival</strong></td><td>❌ No</td><td>✅ Killed zombies may return <abbr class="src-cl" title="Source: mod changelog — not personally verified">📜 changelog</abbr></td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Witch spawning</strong></td><td>✅ Normal</td><td>❌ Witches do not spawn <abbr class="src-cl" title="Source: mod changelog — not personally verified">📜 changelog</abbr></td></tr>
  <tr><td><strong>Difficulty</strong></td><td>Ideal for learning</td><td>Ultimate, uncompromising challenge</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Advice:</strong> If you're new to MITE:BE, <strong>start in Simple mode</strong> to learn. Hardcore mode is for experienced players — the mechanical differences are significant, and one mistake is permanent!</div>

<h2 id="new-mechanics-en">New Mechanics</h2>
<p>MITE:BE introduces many new systems on top of vanilla Minecraft:</p>

<h3 id="temperature-en">Body Temperature</h3>
<p>Optimal body temperature is 36–37°C. Fire, lava, and the Nether raise it — water, rain, and ice lower it. Sunstroke and freezing are real dangers.</p>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Temperature</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(100,180,255,0.12)"><td><strong>&lt;35.8°C</strong></td><td>Cold status — slight slowdown</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(100,200,100,0.10)"><td><strong>36–37°C</strong></td><td>✅ Optimal — no debuffs</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,200,0,0.10)"><td><strong>37.2–38.1°C</strong></td><td>Weakness I</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,150,50,0.12)"><td><strong>38.2–39°C</strong></td><td>Weakness I + Fire + Slowness I + 1 HP/minute</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,80,30,0.14)"><td><strong>39–45°C+</strong></td><td>Weakness I + Fire + Slowness I + 1 HP/20s</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="warning-box">🔥 <strong>Furnace proximity = overheating!</strong> Standing within 2–3 blocks of a burning furnace can push your body temperature above 37.2°C → <strong>Weakness I</strong>. In early game this makes fighting animals impossible too! Fix: step away from the furnace, or manage your temperature with cooling (work near water, hold ice).</div>
<div class="tip-card">🌡️ <strong>Modifiers (warming):</strong> Lava (within 2 blocks): +0.1°C/35s · Fire (within 3 blocks): +0.1°C/50s · Holding a torch: +0.1°C/60s · On fire: +0.1°C/5s · the Nether: constant +0.4°C · Sprinting: +0.1°C/90s (capped at 37°C) · Desert daytime: +0.1°C/hour<br>🌡️ <strong>Modifiers (cooling):</strong> Submerging in water: −0.1°C/5s · Holding ice: −0.1°C/25s · Eating ice cream: −0.1°C · Sleeping on ground: −0.2–0.4°C (random)</div>

<h3 id="curses-en">Curses &amp; Ailments</h3>
<p>Witches can inflict 16 different curses. You must kill that specific witch to remove it, or use a dispel potion. Only one curse is active at a time:</p>
<div class="info-box">🎮 <strong>Hardcore mode:</strong> Witches <strong>do not spawn</strong> in Hardcore mode — this mechanic is inactive there.</div>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Curse Type</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td>Corrosive Skin</td><td>All equipment durability consumption doubled</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td>Can't Hold Breath</td><td>Max underwater oxygen reduced to 30% (3 bubble capacity)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td>Can't Sprint</td><td>Sprinting completely disabled</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td>Can't Eat Meat</td><td>Unable to consume any animal products</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5</td><td>Can't Eat Vegetables</td><td>Unable to consume plant-based foods</td></tr>
  <tr><td>6</td><td>Can't Drink Soup</td><td>Unable to consume soups or stews</td></tr>
  <tr><td>7</td><td>Enderman Hatred</td><td>All Endermen attack unprovoked</td></tr>
  <tr><td>8</td><td>Reduced Intelligence</td><td>−20 effective level penalty (~25% crafting quality penalty)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>9</td><td>Plant Phobia</td><td>60% speed reduction through plant blocks; 80% through vines</td></tr>
  <tr><td>10</td><td>Armor Rejection</td><td>Cannot wear armor; equipped items are expelled</td></tr>
  <tr><td>11</td><td>Chest Phobia</td><td>Cannot open chests</td></tr>
  <tr><td>12</td><td>Can't Sleep</td><td>Can lie in bed but will not fall asleep</td></tr>
  <tr><td>13</td><td>Spider Phobia</td><td>Only 25% chance to deal damage to spiders</td></tr>
  <tr><td>14</td><td>Wolf Phobia</td><td>Only 25% chance to deal damage to wolves</td></tr>
  <tr><td>15</td><td>Creeper Phobia</td><td>Only 25% chance to deal damage to creepers</td></tr>
  <tr><td>16</td><td>Undead Phobia</td><td>Only 25% chance to deal damage to undead mobs</td></tr>
</table>

<h3 id="diabetes-en">Diabetes</h3>
<p>Eating fruits, sugar, and sweets fills an insulin resistance meter (+4,800 per sweet food). It decays naturally (1,200/minute). Milk does <strong>not</strong> cure it!</p>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Threshold</th><th>Level</th><th>Duration</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
  <tr><td>48,000</td><td>Mild</td><td>40–80 min</td><td>Nausea I (20s) after each sweet food</td></tr>
  <tr><td>96,000</td><td>Moderate</td><td>80–120 min</td><td>Nausea II (20s) after each sweet food</td></tr>
  <tr><td>144,000</td><td>Severe</td><td>120–160 min</td><td>Nausea III + Poison (5–10s) after each sweet food</td></tr>
</table>

<h3 id="heat-stroke-en">Heat Stroke</h3>
<p>Being in a desert for 60+ seconds, or near lava (within 2 blocks) for 40+ seconds: <strong>Weakness II + Slowness II</strong> + food provides no nutrition (indefinitely until cured). Cure: bowl of hot water or sugar water.</p>

<h3 id="quality-en">Quality System</h3>
<p>Crafted items have <strong>quality tiers</strong>. Right-click to select a higher quality (costs more XP). Quality primarily affects <strong>durability</strong>:</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Quality</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:#888">Wretched</td><td>Worst durability — avoid if possible</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:#aaa">Poor</td><td>Below-average durability</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:#ccc">Average</td><td>Base durability, free</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--green)">Fine</td><td>+50% durability</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--gold)">Excellent</td><td>+100% durability</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--accent2)">Superb</td><td>+150% durability</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--mithril)">Masterwork</td><td>+200% durability</td></tr>
  <tr><td style="color:var(--adamantium)">Legendary</td><td>+250% durability (Mithril/Adamantium only)</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Normal quality crafting is free (0 XP).</strong> Only higher quality tiers cost XP, and the benefit is primarily increased <strong>durability</strong>. Plan your XP budget wisely!</div>

