<h3 id="gelatinous-cube-en">Gelatinous Cube Block Dissolution</h3>
<p>Small Gelatinous Cube (Jelly) creatures can dissolve blocks with two types of substances: <strong>Pepsin</strong> and <strong>Acid</strong>. 400 ticks ≈ 20 seconds. Knowing which materials are safe is critical for base building!</p>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Material</th><th>Pepsin</th><th>Acid</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(100,200,100,0.10)"><td><strong>Stone, Cobblestone, Obsidian</strong></td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>Best building materials</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(100,200,100,0.10)"><td><strong>Glass, Sandstone, Brick</strong></td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>Fully immune</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(100,200,100,0.10)"><td><strong>Block of Gold 🥇</strong></td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>Surprising — immune!</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(100,200,100,0.10)"><td><strong>Mithril / Adam. / Block of Ancient Metal</strong></td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>Endgame materials</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,200,0,0.08)"><td><strong>Copper, Silver, Block of Iron</strong></td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>⚠️ 400 ticks</td><td>Acid-vulnerable!</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,200,0,0.08)"><td><strong>Wood, Doors, Fences, Ladders, Chests</strong></td><td>✅ Safe</td><td>⚠️ 400 ticks</td><td>Acid dissolves them</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,100,100,0.10)"><td><strong>Wool, Carpet</strong></td><td>⚠️ 400 ticks</td><td>❌ Instant</td><td>Vulnerable to both!</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,100,100,0.10)"><td><strong>Cobweb</strong></td><td>❌ Instant</td><td>❌ Instant</td><td>Dissolves fastest</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,100,100,0.10)"><td><strong>Bed</strong></td><td>⚠️ 400 ticks</td><td>⚠️ 400 ticks</td><td>Don't leave beds exposed!</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="info-box">🏠 <strong>Base building tip:</strong> Bases built from stone, cobblestone, Obsidian, and glass blocks are fully protected against Gelatinous Cubes. Surprisingly, <strong>Blocks of Gold</strong> are also immune — but Copper and Silver blocks are acid-vulnerable.</div>

<h3 id="sleepiness-en">Drowsiness</h3>
<p>The Drowsiness meter increases by 1 per in-game hour. Sleep reduces it. <strong>In the Nether</strong>, the accumulation rate is halved. At 0–7, you gain a <strong>+10% movement speed bonus</strong>!</p>
<table class="compare-table">
  <tr><th>Level</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(100,200,100,0.10)"><td><strong>0–59</strong></td><td>No debuff (0–7: +10% speed bonus)</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,200,0,0.10)"><td><strong>60</strong></td><td>Weakness I</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,150,50,0.12)"><td><strong>80</strong></td><td>Weakness I + Slowness I</td></tr>
  <tr style="background:rgba(255,80,30,0.14)"><td><strong>100+</strong></td><td>Weakness I + Slowness I + Mining Fatigue + 1 HP/hour</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="warning-box">😴 <strong>Early game warning:</strong> The meter rises by 1 per hour — meaning you <strong>must sleep roughly every 2.5 in-game days</strong>. Weakness I isn't just bad for combat: <strong>you can't effectively kill animals either!</strong></div>
<div class="warning-box">🌙 <strong>Beds do NOT skip the night!</strong> In MITE:BE, neither sleeping in a bed nor sleeping on the ground skips the night — it only reduces Drowsiness. You must survive through the night!</div>
<div class="tip-card">🛏️ <strong>Simple Sleep Bag</strong> (v0.8+): 3× matching-color wool → Simple Sleep Bag (16 colors). Place anywhere, right-click to lie down. <strong>Does not set your respawn point.</strong> Main benefit: avoids the ground-sleep debuffs.</div>

<h3 id="foggy-weather-en">Foggy Weather (v0.9.0)</h3>
<p>Fog cannot appear within the first 7 days. It occurs at least once every 50 days and lasts 48–72 hours. <strong>Fortune III bonus</strong> during fog — Fortune III pickaxe gives you Fortune VI!</p>
<div class="warning-box">⚗️ <strong>3 simultaneous hazards active during fog:</strong></div>
